                                <condition>This pillar was reused as a lintel in the construction of a souterrain. The edges of the stone are very rough and uneven. Brash (1879, 145) recorded the height as 6ft. (1.83m). The current visible extent above the display stand is 1.35m.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="vertical" rend="arris_up">The inscription reads upwards on the dexter/left angle of one of the flat faces occupying roughly the middle third of that angle.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>The ogham strokes in this inscription are so fine that they appear to have been <rs type="execution" key="scored">knife-scored</rs> with breaks in the strokes where the stone surface is uneven. Macalister remarked that <q>the notches of the final I are rather long, and misled early decipherers into reading the letter as Q. Brash makes the A into O, but there is only one notch</q> (1945, 73). 
                                <height/>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
